The Central Bureau of Investigation had launched a fresh probe into the murder of whistleblower Satish Shetty |  conducting raids and searches at 21 offices of the Mumbai-based Ideal Road Builders (IRB) Infrastructure Developers Limited across Mumbai |  Pune and Lonavala. CBI is re-investigating the complaint of massive land-grab filed by slain RTI activist against Virendra Mhaiskar |  chairman and managing director of IRB. Satish was hacked to death outside his home in Talegaon in January 2010. He had complained with the Lonavala city police against 13 people |  including Mhaiskar and a sub-registrar |  on October 15 |  2009 |  accusing the company and its subsidiary |  Aryan Infrastructure Investment Pvt. Ltd. |  of acquiring nearly 1 | 100 acres of government and private land in Maval Taluk by forging documents and manipulating land records. Link: https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/Whistleblower-Satish-Shetty%E2%80%99s-death-CBI-opens-fresh-probe-raids-IRB-offices/article60344130.ece

The Punjab Police had launched a manhunt for Gurdeep Singh Jujhar |  the ‘absconding’ owner of Fastway Transmissions Private Limited |  the largest company providing cable TV services in Punjab. Police teams had over the last three days conducted multiple raids at Jujhar’s residence in Ludhiana and also of his company’s employees in other districts.Jujhar had been named as an accused in two of ten FIRs registered against Fastway employees and operators.Jujhar and his associates have been booked in an attempt to murder FIR in Patiala on November 13 |  on the complaint of a cable operator alleging that he was attacked as he decided to work with some other company. In another FIR registered on November 16 at Sirhind in Fatehgarh Sahib |  Jujhar was nominated as an accused for allegedly cutting and stealing cable wires of a rival firm.In another FIR registered at Mohali on November 23 |  Jujhar has also been named in the FIR for weaving a conspiracy to snatch a gold chain and Rs 10 | 000 cash. Link: https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/chandigarh/punjab-police-raids-cable-gurdeep-singh-jujhar-majithia-emergency-9061800/
